          "gradingRecords" : [
            {
              "feedbackGenerated" : "Your thesis on social media’s impact on adolescent mental health is clear, specific, and sets up a compelling argument. The use of the Twenge study demonstrates strong engagement with course readings, and your real-world examples effectively illustrate the data. Your essay is well-organized overall, though the transition between your third and fourth paragraphs could be smoother. In your introduction, watch for passive voice constructions (“it was found that” → “researchers found that”). Your citations are formatted correctly throughout. For your next essay, take more time with the conclusion—currently it feels somewhat rushed compared to the development in your body paragraphs.",
              "gradedAt" : "2026-04-10T14:30:00Z",
              "gradingDurationSeconds" : 185,
              "id" : "87A70FCF-DCDA-49E9-B36D-6B3DE7E8C75B",
              "selections" : [
                "D1F1EEA1-357A-48FB-A1FD-DCABA4B3FCD1",
                "E2915272-539D-4602-B3F2-DB91CCFCB7BC",
                "DFB94335-F9D9-4C57-8883-3A28E4C721A4",
                "6ECF39AC-E4B9-4139-A5FA-7C7B3845D3AB",
                "60411FEC-BADC-4C49-8013-91A218D68251",
                "A8D4ABB7-D771-4E18-A898-A65CD3D515CD",
                "16379028-106E-4DD9-91BA-7487D56D8742",
                "247AB7D1-BBEF-4D7D-B993-A40E68B6BDF0"
              ],
              "studentName" : "Emma Johnson",
              "totalPoints" : 26,
              "transcript" : "Really strong thesis here. The argument about social media and mental health is clear and specific. Good use of the Twenge study from the readings. I like how she connects the data to real-world examples. Organization is solid but the transition between paragraphs 3 and 4 is a bit abrupt. Watch passive voice in the intro. Citation format is perfect. Conclusion could be stronger - feels a bit rushed."
            },
            {
              "feedbackGenerated" : "Your essay addresses technology in education, but the thesis needs to be more specific and take a clearer argumentative position. Rather than stating that “technology affects education,” specify how and why, and make an arguable claim. Your evidence is limited—draw more substantially from course readings rather than relying on outside blog sources. When you do cite sources, push your analysis deeper; explain not just what the source says, but why it matters for your argument. Your organizational structure is solid with a clear introduction, body paragraphs, and conclusion. For the next draft, review comma usage and watch for sentence fragments. Your citation format is correct—continue using it consistently.",
              "gradedAt" : "2026-04-10T14:35:00Z",
              "gradingDurationSeconds" : 210,
              "id" : "B2A4D43B-7BD8-4BE0-B4D8-737412736B22",
              "selections" : [
                "60411FEC-BADC-4C49-8013-91A218D68251",
                "CD21584D-9909-43DB-95F2-613D88E0856B",
                "D1F1EEA1-357A-48FB-A1FD-DCABA4B3FCD1",
                "1E4B70DB-07F4-42A6-BE6C-A407FBD535BE",
                "DFB94335-F9D9-4C57-8883-3A28E4C721A4",
                "4F8D38CE-4DA2-4616-9764-FFF1DBDDE8E2",
                "16379028-106E-4DD9-91BA-7487D56D8742",
                "247AB7D1-BBEF-4D7D-B993-A40E68B6BDF0"
              ],
              "studentName" : "Liam Chen",
              "totalPoints" : 22,
              "transcript" : "Thesis is there but it's pretty vague. Says technology affects education but doesn't specify how or take a clear position. Needs more evidence from the readings - only cites one source and it's from a random blog. The analysis of that source is superficial. Organization is actually pretty good though. Clear intro, body paragraphs, conclusion. Some grammar issues - missing commas, a few fragments. Citations are in the right format at least."
            },
            {
              "feedbackGenerated" : "This is excellent work. Your thesis on climate policy is sophisticated and takes a nuanced position that you sustain throughout the essay. You integrate multiple course sources seamlessly, and your counterargument section is particularly strong—you acknowledge opposing perspectives and refute them convincingly. Your organizational structure is flawless, with natural transitions that guide readers smoothly through your argument. The writing is clear, engaging, and nearly error-free (I noted only two minor typos). This represents A-level work. For your next essay, continue building on this approach and consider pushing your analysis even further in places where you summarize source material.",
              "gradedAt" : "2026-04-10T14:42:00Z",
              "gradingDurationSeconds" : 195,
              "id" : "B3DF05E2-FF6D-4BED-84CE-8FD38DFF199B",
              "selections" : [
                "16379028-106E-4DD9-91BA-7487D56D8742",
                "F8C503B7-6E31-438B-976C-62A4223EE341",
