                "2E5401C6-30E0-40B1-A9BA-F3DE7D482410"
              ],
              "studentName" : "Sophia Rodriguez",
              "totalPoints" : 29,
              "transcript" : "Excellent work. Thesis on climate policy is sophisticated and nuanced. Uses multiple sources from the readings and integrates them seamlessly. The counterargument section is particularly strong - acknowledges opposing views and refutes them convincingly. Organization is flawless. Transitions are natural and guide the reader through the argument. Writing style is clear and engaging. Only spotted two minor typos. This is A-level work."
            },
            {
              "feedbackGenerated" : "Your thesis needs clarification—I’m not sure what argumentative position you’re taking on this topic. In your body paragraphs, ideas jump between topics without clear connections; each paragraph should have one main point that builds toward your overall argument. You include evidence from sources, but much of it is paraphrased without original analysis. Rather than stating “the author says X,” explain why X matters and how it supports your claim. Strengthen your organization by ensuring each paragraph builds logically on the previous one. Review your sentences for run-ons, and make your citation format consistent throughout (several are missing page numbers). For your next draft, outline your argument first to ensure a clear through-line from thesis to conclusion.",
              "gradedAt" : "2026-04-10T14:48:00Z",
              "gradingDurationSeconds" : 220,
              "id" : "4B9F871A-BA8D-4E7A-9177-42DF9C98B710",
              "selections" : [
                "DFB94335-F9D9-4C57-8883-3A28E4C721A4",
