                "FB7F665E-95D5-475E-9F1B-141C019315EB"
              ],
              "studentName" : "Noah Patel",
              "totalPoints" : 19,
              "transcript" : "Thesis is unclear - can't tell what position he's actually taking. Body paragraphs jump around between different ideas without clear connections. Evidence is there but it's mostly paraphrased without much original analysis. Lots of \"the author says\" without explaining so what. Organization is weak - paragraphs don't build on each other. Some run-on sentences. Citations are inconsistent - some are formatted right, others are missing page numbers."
            },
            {
              "feedbackGenerated" : "Your thesis on income inequality takes a clear position and sets up your argument effectively. You engage with three sources from the syllabus, demonstrating strong preparation. Your analysis is solid, though in several places you tend toward summary rather than deeper critical engagement—ask yourself “why does this matter?” and “what are the implications?” Your organizational structure is sound, with introduction and conclusion that align well. Some body paragraphs would benefit from stronger topic sentences that explicitly connect to your thesis. The writing is clear with only a few comma splices to address. Your citations are formatted correctly. For the next essay, focus on pushing past summary to offer more original analysis of your sources.",
              "gradedAt" : "2026-04-10T14:55:00Z",
              "gradingDurationSeconds" : 175,
              "id" : "B88C9716-1978-4FB7-9DF5-0F79C18F2DD6",
              "selections" : [
